SIMPLE: lope
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lope
<hw>Lope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>imp.</pos> <def>of <er>Leap</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And, laughing, <qex>lope</qex> into a tree.
<qex>Spenser</qex>.</q>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lope</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lope
<hw>Lope</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Loped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Loping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See <er>Leap</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To leap; to dance.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧He that <xex>lopes</xex> on the ropes.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Middleton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To move with a leaping or bounding stride, as a
horse.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To run with an easy, bounding stride; -- of
people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lope</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Lope
<hw>Lope</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A leap; a long step.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An easy gait, consisting of long running strides or
leaps.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mustang goes rollicking ahead, with the eternal
<qex>lope</qex>, . . . a mixture of two or three gaits, as easy as the
motions of a cradle.</q> <rj><qau>T. B. Thorpe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lop-eared</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Lopeared</ent>⟦br⟧
